Shunjôbô ... conceived the idea of having both priests and laymen add
the Namu Amida Butsu to their given names, in order that when they would
be kneeling before Emma, the king of the lower world, and were asked by
him what their names were, they could reply in the language of this prayer
(and so escape his wrath).
